This paper deals with the optimization of a communication system involving a UAV and multiple ground base stations, which falls under the category of networked systems and control (cs.NI) and robotics (cs.RO). The optimization problem involves a quality of connectivity constraint, which requires the use of information theory (cs.IT) and control theory (cs.SY). The proposed algorithm also leverages techniques in convex optimization (cs.LG).
